#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an9.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an9.41:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.41:0.2"
msgid "4. Mahāvagga "
msgstr "4. The Great Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 41. Tapussasutta → tapussagahapatisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an9.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Tapussasutta "
msgstr "41. With the Householder Tapussa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an9.41:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā mallesu viharati uruvelakappaṃ nāma mallānaṃ nigamo. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Mallas, near the Mallian town named Uruvelakappa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.41:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya uruvelakappaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Uruvelakappa for alms. "

msgctxt "an9.41:1.3"
msgid "Uruvelakappe piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he addressed Venerable Ānanda, "

msgctxt "an9.41:1.4"
msgid "“idheva tāva tvaṃ, ānanda, hohi, yāvāhaṃ mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhāmi divāvihārāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Ānanda, you stay right here, while I plunge deep into the Great Wood for the day’s meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an9.41:1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. "

msgctxt "an9.41:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha plunged deep into the Great Wood and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an9.41:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho tapusso gahapati yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho tapusso gahapati āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The householder Tapussa went up to Venerable Ānanda, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an9.41:3.1"
msgid "“Mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, gihī kāmabhogino kāmārāmā kāmaratā kāmasammuditā. "
msgstr "“Sir, Ānanda, we are laypeople who enjoy sensual pleasures. We like sensual pleasures, we love them and take joy in them. "

msgctxt "an9.41:3.2"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ kāmārāmānaṃ kāmaratānaṃ kāmasammuditānaṃ papāto viya khāyati, yadidaṃ nekkhammaṃ. "
msgstr "But renunciation seems like an abyss. "

# NOTE: See BB’s note on reading adhimuccati.
#. VAR: passato → passataṃ (?)
msgctxt "an9.41:3.3"
msgid "Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, ‘imasmiṃ dhammavinaye daharānaṃ daharānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "I have heard that in this teaching and training there are very young mendicants whose minds are eager for renunciation; they’re confident, settled, and decided about it. They see it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:3.4"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye bhikkhūnaṃ bahunā janena visabhāgo, yadidaṃ nekkhamman”ti. "
msgstr "Renunciation is the dividing line between the multitude and the mendicants in this teaching and training.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.439, sc4
msgctxt "an9.41:4.1"
msgid "“Atthi kho etaṃ, gahapati, kathāpābhataṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya. "
msgstr "“Householder, we should see the Buddha about this matter. "

msgctxt "an9.41:4.2"
msgid "Āyāma, gahapati, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamissāma; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocessāma. "
msgstr "Come, let’s go to the Buddha and inform him about this. "

msgctxt "an9.41:4.3"
msgid "Yathā no bhagavā byākarissati tathā naṃ dhāressāmā”ti. "
msgstr "As he answers, so we’ll remember it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an9.41:5.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho tapusso gahapati āyasmato ānandassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Tapussa. "

msgctxt "an9.41:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando tapussena gahapatinā saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Ānanda together with Tapussa went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Ānanda told him what had happened. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an9.41:6.1"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, bhante, tapusso gahapati evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.41:6.2"
msgid "‘mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, gihī kāmabhogino kāmārāmā kāmaratā kāmasammuditā, tesaṃ no, bhante, amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ kāmabhogīnaṃ kāmārāmānaṃ kāmaratānaṃ kāmasammuditānaṃ papāto viya khāyati, yadidaṃ nekkhammaṃ’. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.41:6.3"
msgid "Sutaṃ metaṃ, bhante, ‘imasmiṃ dhammavinaye daharānaṃ daharānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an9.41:6.4"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhante, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye bhikkhūnaṃ bahunā janena visabhāgo yadidaṃ nekkhamman’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.440, sc7
msgctxt "an9.41:7.1"
msgid "“Evametaṃ, ānanda, evametaṃ, ānanda. "
msgstr "“That’s so true, Ānanda! That’s so true! "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.2"
msgid "Mayhampi kho, ānanda, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.3"
msgid "‘sādhu nekkhammaṃ, sādhu paviveko’ti. "
msgstr "‘Renunciation is good! Seclusion is good!’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, nekkhamme cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "But my mind wasn’t eager for renunciation; it wasn’t confident, settled, and decided about it. I didn’t see it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.5"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.6"
msgid "‘ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo, yena me nekkhamme cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’? "
msgstr "‘What is the cause, what is the reason why my mind isn’t eager for renunciation, and not confident, settled, and decided about it? Why don’t I see it as peaceful?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.8"
msgid "‘kāmesu kho me ādīnavo adiṭṭho, so ca me abahulīkato, nekkhamme ca ānisaṃso anadhigato, so ca me anāsevito. "
msgstr "‘I haven’t seen the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, and so I haven’t cultivated that. I haven’t realized the benefits of renunciation, and so I haven’t developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.9"
msgid "Tasmā me nekkhamme cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "That’s why my mind isn’t eager for renunciation, and not confident, settled, and decided about it. And it’s why I don’t see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.10"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

#. VAR: bahulaṃ kareyyaṃ → bahulīkareyyaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an9.41:7.11"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ kāmesu ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulaṃ kareyyaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseveyyaṃ, "
msgstr "‘Suppose that, seeing the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, I were to cultivate that. And suppose that, realizing the benefits of renunciation, I were to develop that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.12"
msgid "ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati yaṃ me nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandeyya pasīdeyya santiṭṭheyya vimucceyya etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "It’s possible that my mind would be eager for renunciation; it would be confident, settled, and decided about it. And I would see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.13"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, aparena samayena kāmesu ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulamakāsiṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseviṃ. "
msgstr "And so, after some time, I saw the drawbacks of sensual pleasures and cultivated that, and I realized the benefits of renunciation and developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.14"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, nekkhamme cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "Then my mind was eager for renunciation; it was confident, settled, and decided about it. I saw it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.15"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi. "
msgstr "And so, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.16"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, iminā vihārena viharato kāmasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "While I was in that meditation, perceptions and attentions accompanied by sensual pleasures beset me, and that was an affliction for me. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.17"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya; "
msgstr "Suppose a happy person were to experience pain; that would be an affliction for them. "

msgctxt "an9.41:7.18"
msgid "evamevassa me kāmasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "In the same way, when perceptions and attentions accompanied by sensual pleasures beset me, that was an affliction for me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.441, sc8
msgctxt "an9.41:8.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled … enter and remain in the second absorption?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, avitakke cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "But my mind wasn’t eager to stop placing the mind; it wasn’t confident, settled, and decided about it. I didn’t see it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.5"
msgid "‘ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo, yena me avitakke cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’? "
msgstr "‘What is the cause, what is the reason why my mind isn’t eager to stop placing the mind, and not confident, settled, and decided about it? Why don’t I see it as peaceful?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.7"
msgid "‘vitakkesu kho me ādīnavo adiṭṭho, so ca me abahulīkato, avitakke ca ānisaṃso anadhigato, so ca me anāsevito. "
msgstr "‘I haven’t seen the drawbacks of placing the mind, and so I haven’t cultivated that. I haven’t realized the benefits of not placing the mind, and so I haven’t developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.8"
msgid "Tasmā me avitakke cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "That’s why my mind isn’t eager to stop placing the mind, and not confident, settled, and decided about it. And it’s why I don’t see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.10"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ vitakkesu ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulaṃ kareyyaṃ, avitakke ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseveyyaṃ, ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati yaṃ me avitakke cittaṃ pakkhandeyya pasīdeyya santiṭṭheyya vimucceyya etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "‘Suppose that, seeing the drawbacks of placing the mind, I were to cultivate that. And suppose that, realizing the benefits of not placing the mind, I were to develop that. It’s possible that my mind would be eager to stop placing the mind; it would be confident, settled, and decided about it. And I would see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.11"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, aparena samayena vitakkesu ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulamakāsiṃ, avitakke ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseviṃ. "
msgstr "And so, after some time, I saw the drawbacks of placing the mind and cultivated that, and I realized the benefits of not placing the mind and developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.12"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, avitakke cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "Then my mind was eager to stop placing the mind; it was confident, settled, and decided about it. I saw it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.13"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi. "
msgstr "And so, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected were stilled … I was entering and remaining in the second absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.14"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, iminā vihārena viharato vitakkasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "While I was in that meditation, perceptions and attentions accompanied by placing the mind beset me, and that was an affliction for me. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.15"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya; "
msgstr "Suppose a happy person were to experience pain; that would be an affliction for them. "

msgctxt "an9.41:8.16"
msgid "evamevassa me vitakkasahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "In the same way, when perceptions and attentions accompanied by placing the mind and keeping it connected beset me, that was an affliction for me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.442, sc9
msgctxt "an9.41:9.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihareyyaṃ sato ca sampajāno sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeyyaṃ yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti—upekkhako satimā sukhavihārīti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, with the fading away of rapture, enter and remain in the third absorption, where I will meditate with equanimity, mindful and aware, personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss”?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, nippītike cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "But my mind wasn’t eager for freedom from rapture; it wasn’t confident, settled, and decided about it. I didn’t see it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.5"
msgid "‘ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo, yena me nippītike cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’? "
msgstr "‘What is the cause, what is the reason why my mind isn’t eager for freedom from rapture, and not confident, settled, and decided about it? Why don’t I see it as peaceful?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.7"
msgid "‘pītiyā kho me ādīnavo adiṭṭho, so ca me abahulīkato, nippītike ca ānisaṃso anadhigato, so ca me anāsevito. "
msgstr "‘I haven’t seen the drawbacks of rapture, and so I haven’t cultivated that. I haven’t realized the benefits of freedom from rapture, and so I haven’t developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.8"
msgid "Tasmā me nippītike cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "That’s why my mind isn’t eager for freedom from rapture, and not confident, settled, and decided about it. And it’s why I don’t see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.10"
msgid "‘sace kho ahaṃ pītiyā ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulaṃ kareyyaṃ, nippītike ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseveyyaṃ, ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ vijjati yaṃ me nippītike cittaṃ pakkhandeyya pasīdeyya santiṭṭheyya vimucceyya etaṃ santanti passato’. "
msgstr "‘Suppose that, seeing the drawbacks of rapture, I were to cultivate that. And suppose that, realizing the benefits of freedom from rapture, I were to develop that. It’s possible that my mind would be eager to be free from rapture; it would be confident, settled, and decided about it. And I would see it as peaceful.’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.11"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, aparena samayena pītiyā ādīnavaṃ disvā taṃ bahulamakāsiṃ, nippītike ānisaṃsaṃ adhigamma tamāseviṃ. "
msgstr "And so, after some time, I saw the drawbacks of rapture and cultivated that, and I realized the benefits of freedom from rapture and developed that. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.12"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, nippītike cittaṃ pakkhandati pasīdati santiṭṭhati vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "Then my mind was eager for freedom from rapture; it was confident, settled, and decided about it. I saw it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.13"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, ānanda, pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi. "
msgstr "And so, with the fading away of rapture … I was entering and remaining in the third absorption. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.14"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, iminā vihārena viharato pītisahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "While I was in that meditation, perceptions and attentions accompanied by rapture beset me, and that was an affliction for me. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.15"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, ānanda, sukhino dukkhaṃ uppajjeyya yāvadeva ābādhāya; "
msgstr "Suppose a happy person were to experience pain; that would be an affliction for them. "

msgctxt "an9.41:9.16"
msgid "evamevassa me pītisahagatā saññāmanasikārā samudācaranti. Svassa me hoti ābādho. "
msgstr "In the same way, when perceptions and attentions accompanied by rapture beset me, that was an affliction for me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.443, sc10
msgctxt "an9.41:10.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, with the giving up of pleasure and pain, and the ending of former happiness and sadness, enter and remain in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, adukkhamasukhe cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato. "
msgstr "But my mind wasn’t eager to be without pleasure and pain; it wasn’t confident, settled, and decided about it. I didn’t see it as peaceful. "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.5"
msgid "‘ko nu kho hetu ko paccayo, yena me adukkhamasukhe cittaṃ na pakkhandati nappasīdati na santiṭṭhati na vimuccati etaṃ santanti passato’? "
msgstr "‘What is the cause, what is the reason why my mind isn’t eager to be without pleasure and pain, and not confident, settled, and decided about it? Why don’t I see it as peaceful?’ "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, ānanda, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then I thought, "

msgctxt "an9.41:10.7"
